    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-aiq-xl py-aiq-4xl">

      <p class="font-mono text-aiq-xs text-aiq-fg-muted tracking-aiq-mono uppercase mb-aiq-md m-0">Who it's for</p>
      <h2 id="usecases-heading" class="font-serif text-aiq-3xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-3xl mt-0">
        Built for teams that want to close the gap, not just identify it.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-aiq-lg">
        {useCases.map(uc => (
          <div class="bg-aiq-bg-base border border-aiq-border rounded-aiq-lg p-aiq-xl">
            <p class="font-mono text-aiq-xs text-aiq-fg-muted tracking-aiq-mono uppercase mb-aiq-md mt-0">
              {uc.label}
            </p>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0 leading-snug">
              {uc.heading}
            </h3>
            <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
              {uc.body}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="bg-aiq-bg-base border-b border-aiq-border" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-aiq-xl py-aiq-4xl">

      <p class="font-mono text-aiq-xs text-aiq-fg-muted tracking-aiq-mono uppercase mb-aiq-md m-0">FAQ</p>
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-serif text-aiq-3xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-3xl mt-0">
        Common questions about team skill-gap assessments.
      </h2>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-aiq-xl max-w-3xl">

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            What is a team skill-gap assessment and how does AssessIQ run one?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            A skill-gap assessment measures where your team's current competencies fall short of what a role or project requires. In AssessIQ, you define the target competency profile for a role, invite team members to complete a structured assessment, and receive individual and cohort-level reports showing where gaps exist. The results feed directly into training plans or internal mobility decisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            Which skills can AssessIQ assess for an existing team?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            AssessIQ covers technical skills (Python, Java, SQL, React, .NET, data analysis, cloud fundamentals), aptitude (quantitative, logical reasoning), and domain knowledge packs. For L&D use cases, assessments are typically less timed and less proctored than hiring screens — the goal is an honest competency map, not a high-stakes gatekeeping event.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            How are team assessment results reported?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            AssessIQ produces individual scorecards and cohort-level reports. The cohort view shows score distributions by band (for example, what percentage of the team meets a "proficient" threshold on Python), per-competency breakdowns, and exportable data for HR systems or training-provider briefings. No individual's data is shared without their awareness.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            Can AssessIQ be used for internal mobility and promotion decisions?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            Yes. AssessIQ's structured rubrics and scoring bands make assessment results usable for internal benchmarking — not just as a number, but as a documented competency profile. For promotion or role-change decisions, the audit trail ensures the decision is backed by consistent evidence, not just a manager's impression.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            How does a skill-gap assessment differ from a hiring assessment on AssessIQ?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            The platform is the same, but the configuration differs. For internal skill-gap work: proctoring is typically lighter or off (employees are not anonymous candidates), time pressure is reduced, and the output is a development profile rather than a pass/fail shortlist. Admins control all three parameters per assessment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">
            Can we benchmark our team against an external standard or role definition?
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            AssessIQ lets you define a target competency profile for a role — the skills, levels, and bands that constitute "ready for this role." Each team member's assessment is then scored against that profile, producing a gap view: who is ready, who needs development in which area, and how much. External benchmarking against industry standards is on the roadmap; today the comparison is against the organisation's own defined role profiles.
            {/* TODO: real data — update when external benchmark library is live */}
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── EXPLORE OTHER SOLUTIONS + CTA ── -->
  <section class="bg-aiq-bg-raised" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-aiq-xl py-aiq-4xl">

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-aiq-4xl items-start">

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-aiq-xs text-aiq-fg-muted tracking-aiq-mono uppercase mb-aiq-md m-0">Get started</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-aiq-2xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-xl mt-0">
            Ready to map your team's skills before planning your next quarter?
          </h2>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-aiq-md mb-aiq-2xl">
            <a
              href="https://assessiq.in/admin/login"
              class="font-sans text-aiq-md font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-aiq-pill bg-aiq-accent text-white
                     hover:bg-aiq-accent-hover transition-colors duration-150
                     focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-aiq-accent focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
            >
              Start free
            </a>
            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="font-sans text-aiq-md font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-aiq-pill border border-aiq-border-strong
                     text-aiq-fg-primary hover:border-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent transition-colors duration-150
                     focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-aiq-accent focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
            >
              Talk to us
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-sm text-aiq-fg-muted leading-relaxed m-0">
            See <a href="/pricing" class="text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover underline underline-offset-2">pricing</a> or review our <a href="/security" class="text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover underline underline-offset-2">security and data residency</a> practices.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Other solutions -->
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-aiq-xs text-aiq-fg-muted tracking-aiq-mono uppercase mb-aiq-md m-0">Other solutions</p>
          <h2 id="related-heading" class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-lg mt-0">
            AssessIQ across every assessment context.
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-none m-0 p-0 flex flex-col gap-aiq-md">
            <li>
              <a href="/solutions/it-hiring" class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover transition-colors">
                IT &amp; Technical Hiring
              </a>
              <p class="font-sans text-aiq-sm text-aiq-fg-muted m-0 mt-aiq-xs">Coding tests, technical screening, and proctored developer assessments for IT companies.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/solutions/campus-recruitment" class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover transition-colors">
                Campus &amp; Fresher Recruitment
              </a>
              <p class="font-sans text-aiq-sm text-aiq-fg-muted m-0 mt-aiq-xs">Aptitude, coding, and English at bulk scale for campus placement drives.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/solutions/educational-institutions" class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover transition-colors">
                Educational Institutions
              </a>
              <p class="font-sans text-aiq-sm text-aiq-fg-muted m-0 mt-aiq-xs">Online proctored exams and skill certification for colleges and universities.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
